other_features.name: Quartz vein
other_features.description: Post deformational intrusion within schist almost all Quartz. Change S thickness. Schist is composed of transparent to pink Quartz  coarse grained biotite and muscovite. There is a diagenic? Orange brown texture in some areas. This outcrop contains very little feldspar. Bedding seems to be upright or slightly overturned. Possibly amphibolite facies but absence of alumino silicates does not allow us to constrain pt conditions.
